		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Metarie, LA 5/25/02 Had to Leave Early..<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.80)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=7058'>Jonathan "Carny" brown</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=7058&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> May 26, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Well fellas, its been a while since I submitted a report for LotR so I figure it&#39;s about time. This weeks tourney was cool, although a bit of a bummer since I was kicking butt and had to leave early since my band was playing at a wedding reception. Such is life, no? <br />
<br />
Pre Tourney<br />
<br />
Well, I have been toying with different ideas for decks, mainly for FP though, since I have been pretty set on Uruks lately. I toyed with Shoulder fire, but decided that I could be screwed by Uruks and also by Tower Assassins, which I have convinced nearly everyone to put in their decks. I looked to Gandalf/Aragorn but found that I still cannot trade for Servants so it came down to Rangers, since that is the only thing I am equiped to play that I feel comfortable with. Well, I realized that with but one exception, nearly everyone was playing Uruks. I hate being like everyone else, so I was looking at the Ferny/Frost deck, I mean c&#39;mon, who can NOT like a 1st turn win, besides, that would make it a possibility that I could finish the tourney. If I can win on the first turn against a couple of people, maybe all my opponents will concede? But, after playtesting it Ferny seemed to be too unreliable. Mainly because if you can&#39;t kill them with Ferny they will move again and again and NO fellowship can win alone. Well, I am at a loss. Moria sucks in our Metagame. You get screwed by Sleep or Sentinels then shot down. I have no Sauron stuff, having traded all of that for Foil Sites and Nazgul. Oh yeah, Nazgul? That&#39;ll be it. So heres the decklist.<br />
<br />
Start<br />
<br />
Frodo, RA<br />
The One Ring, IB<br />
Arwen, DoE<br />
Legolas, G<br />
<br />
Prancing Pony<br />
Weatherhills<br />
Ford of Bruinen<br />
Moria Lake<br />
The Bridge<br />
Valley of Silverlode<br />
Silverlode Banks<br />
Anduin Banks<br />
Summit of Amon Hin<br />
<br />
Companions<br />
<br />
Aragorn, KiE x 4<br />
Sam, SoH<br />
<br />
Allies<br />
<br />
Elrond, LoR x 4<br />
Thrarin, DS<br />
Orophin, Dude<br />
<br />
Possessions<br />
<br />
Ranger&#39;s Sword<br />
Flaming Brand<br />
Gwemegil<br />
Asfaloth<br />
Sting x 2<br />
Thror&#39;s Map x 2<br />
Aragorn&#39;s Bow x 2<br />
<br />
Conditions<br />
<br />
The Tale of Gil-Galad<br />
The Saga of Elendil<br />
O Elebreth! Gilthoniel!<br />
The Last Alliance of Elves and Men<br />
Gift of Boats<br />
<br />
Events<br />
<br />
PATHS x 2<br />
ARV x 2<br />
Secret Sentinels x 3<br />
<br />
Minions<br />
<br />
The Witch King, LoA x 4<br />
Ulaire Attea x 3<br />
Ulaire Toldea x 3<br />
Ulaire Cantea x 3<br />
Ulaire Nelya x 3<br />
Ulaire Enquea x 2<br />
Ulaire Lemenya x 2<br />
<br />
Possessions<br />
<br />
The Pale Blade x 2<br />
<br />
Conditions<br />
<br />
Black Breath x 3<br />
<br />
Events<br />
<br />
All Blades Perish x 4<br />
Fear x 2<br />
Morgul gates x 4<br />
<br />
pretty much Nazgul beatdown with running rangers. If this deck needs any explaining, ask me but I think it&#39;s pretty straitforward.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
anyways, I arrived at BSI Comics II around 11:30 and bought a few packs. Got a Double Shot and nothing much else. Traded for a Gandalf FotS, a Foil site and some others and the games were under way.<br />
<br />
Game 1  vs. Damon<br />
Gandalf, TGP start / mixed shadow<br />
<br />
well, Damon and I bid with him bidding 2 to my 1 and he chooses to go first, which is good since I would have made him go first anyways, He plays Aragorn, Gimli, Glamdring and Nice Imitation and Gladrings me. He sees Morgul Gates, Witch King, Pale Blade, Cantea and Black Breath. He moves. I proceed to kill gimli, wound Aragorn twice and Breath and wound Gandalf. He stops. I play Aragorn, Tale of G, Bow and Orophin then move. I shoot down his stuff and move again, facing a random Uruk at Frodo&#39;s Bedroom. he plays I think Elrond and then moves. I gates Nelya, change the site and drop Toldea. He getshimmer a few times but loses noone. Stops. I play Sam, Map and Last Alliance, Elrond and Gift of Boats and move to my Moria Lake. Face 3 or four Uruks and kill them but stop because I feel pretty confident about Shadow. He plays Legolas, PoM and Boromir, SoD and moves. I drop Witch King and Pale Blade and Nelya. He manages to survive, but won&#39;t move again. I move to bridge and face Balrog, DB. Sam and Thrarin die and I move to my Valley, holding two ARVs. He plays a couple of guys and I feed him Orophin, who is exhausted anyway. He moves to bridge and face Attea. I Breath Gandaleasterlingain(stupid Athelas) and ends up losing Boromir and Legolas because Attea can pump! I move from Valley to Banks, facing little or nothing but don&#39;t use the boats to move again because it doesn&#39;t matter at this point. He moves, loses nothing cause all I can play is Nelya and he stops because he can&#39;t catch me. I move into the Summit and shoot down his Uruks because he exerted them to play 2 or three conditions that did no good. Secret Sentinels rocks!<br />
<br />
FW +3 (3)<br />
<br />
Highs: Witch King w/ Blade on turn 1!<br />
Lows: not a good game for Damon.<br />
<br />
Game 2 Fred<br />
Hobbits/ Moria (just got some Armories)<br />
<br />
well, Fred got the bye first round and he had some time to finish working on his decks. He doesn&#39;t know what to expect from me, but he did lose the last tournament to my Mr. Took Superstar deck. Well, I bid my 1, he bids 4 and he plays the Hobbitton Party Field. Out comes Bilbo, RA and a Party Guest. He also plays O Elbereth, which bites for me. He moves and I play Witch King and Nelya, using Gates on both. Proceeds to lose Sam and Pippin on the first turn, having to ditch O Elbereth to not lose Frodo. He stops. I play a good bit of stuff, including the Last Alliance. He plays a Scavengers and a Sneak and I shoot them and move again, mainly because I have a Nelya in my hand to get the Ford back. He plays the Witch King Twilight, which is surprising. I let him win his fight and wound Frodo twice, which doesn;t matter since I am at a sanctuary. Well, he loses Merry at the bridge but manages to survive all the way through site 6 with just Frodo because he is able to play 3 copies of O Eleberth!!!!!! I was so mad, but anyways I know I can move slow and still win, just gets frustrating for the Nazgul. The highlight of this game was when he played at the Bridge 2 orcs, the Balrog and the Witch King. I had to lose Legolas, but hey it doesn&#39;t matter. I finnaly managed to get through all his Stealth stuff at site 7, where he had to exert Frodo at the banks, preventing him from using Filbert.<br />
<br />
FW +3 (6)<br />
<br />
Highs: I love winning with Shadow<br />
Lows: Taking SO LONG to win with Shadow.<br />
<br />
Game 3 Shawn<br />
Boromir, Merry start/ Sauron<br />
<br />
Shawn has apparently won his first two ganes, since noone is prepared to deal with Sauron. The only thing wierd was that he never played an UTWE the whole game. Dunno if he never saw one or if he just doesn&#39;t play them. Anyways, he goes first with the Pony, plays Aragorn, Bow and moves. I play Witch King w/ Pale Blade and Cantea(noticing a patern here?) and kill Merry after he hides from one fight. He shoots Cantea down because he doesn&#39;t want to lose the Bow. He Stops. I move and he plays a Bowmen and an Orc who dies. I stop because I have no Nelya or Map. He moves and fights ANOTHER Witch King and has to lose Boromir. Already down to just Aragorn and Frodo. Well, on my turn I play Elrond, Orophin and use Elrond to draw Gift of Boats, Elrond and Secret Sentinels. HE HE.<br />
I movem he plays another Bowmen and a guy, I Sentinels it and shoot down his guy, then stop to heal. He moves and faces nothing he can&#39;t handle. I move, hoping for another Sentinels but don&#39;t get one. He plays a Morgul Hunter who Hates Legolas twice and then makes Aragorn Depseratly Defend the Ring. The Hunter dies to Archery. He plays Legolas, G and moves to the Bridge where he fights the Witch King and Nelya. Witch King gets shot and Nelya dies. He Stops. I move to the Bridge and face 2 or three Orcs and another Bowmen, Luckily, I drew a Sentinels. I play it to ditch DDotR and Bowmen. He Then loses all of his men to archery. I stop, since I have Gift of Boats, He moves to 6, exhausting his companions in the process but losing noone. I move to 6 and kill the 3 trackers he plays. He double jumps to 8, using 2 ARV in the process and I can&#39;t really stop him but it doesn&#39;t matter since I have Gift of Boats, Asfaloth, 2 ARV, Thrors Map and 2 PATHS in my hand. I proceed to move from 6 to 9, facing very little since Shawn had ALL fellowship in his hand. Sucks to be Shawn.<br />
<br />
FW +3 (9)<br />
<br />
Highs: Gift of Boats<br />
Lows: I have to leave after this game!<br />
<br />
<br />
so that is the end of this tourney. I KNOW I would have won, but such is life! I don&#39;t know who ended up winning although when I left Rob was in the lead. As wierd as it seems, Lurtz with his Sword tends to kill anything and everyhting he runs into. Thanks for reading and if you need anything, ask me!<br />
<br />
Jonathan, the Carny<br />
Decipher rated 1811 (always wanted to do that) <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3688&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
